ich firm can show low D/E yet still be risky elsewhere."},{"label":"Earnings momentum","value":-34.78,"unit":"% YoY","status":"weak","read":"Profit down 35% YoY (latest TTM).","meaning":"Trailing-twelve-month net profit vs the year-ago TTM (and whether the YoY rate is rising = 'accelerating').","why_useful":"Improving, accelerating earnings tend to drive re-rating; falling profit warns of a deteriorating business.","why_it_can_fail":"TTM can be lumpy for cyclicals/one-offs; cross-check the multi-year trend on the Fundamentals tab."}]},"valuation":{"ok":true,"is_bank":false,"pe_now":12.8,"pe_percentile":74.0,"median_pe":11.1,"earnings_yield_pct":7.81,"pb":1.16,"ev_ebitda":8.72,"quality_score":61.0,"pat_cagr_5y_pct":6.8,"peg":1.87,"cheapness":{"status":"weak","read":"P/E at the 74-percentile of its 10-yr range \u2014 expensive vs its own history."},"expectations":"At 12.8\u00d7 earnings for ~7% 5-yr profit CAGR, the market is paying \u22481.87\u00d7 growth (PEG). >2 = a lot already priced in; <1 = cheap if growth holds.","cyclical_caveat":null,"meaning":"P/E percentile = where today's price-to-earnings sits within the stock's own last-10-yr range (low = cheap vs its past). Paired with the Quality score and 5-yr profit growth so a cheap multiple is judged against business strength, not in isolation.","why_useful":"Cheapness only matters relative to quality and growth \u2014 a low P/E on a declining or peak-cyclical business is a trap, not a bargain.","why_it_can_fail":"P/E breaks for loss-makers / one-offs; for banks use P/B not EV/EBITDA; a multiple cheap vs history can stay cheap if the business has structurally de-rated."},"ownership":{"ok":true,"na":null,"holders":{"Promoter":{"periods":["Jun 2023","Sep 2023","Dec 2023","Mar 2024","Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[74.53,74.53,74.53,74.53,74.53,71.77,71.78,71.78,71.78,71.78,71.78,71.78],"latest_pct":71.78,"chg_1y_pp":0.0},"FII":{"periods":["Jun 2023","